# 1. 今、できることを

Haruka: Huff... Huff... Huff...
Haruka: (Oh, I passed my usual turn.)
Haruka: I need to focus more...
Haruka: (But...)
Haruka: (I can't get what's been happening out of my head.)
Haruka: (Why is it that we haven't received a single offer since performing at Idol Lovers?)
Haruka: (The crowd there that day responded so well, and so did everyone on social media...)
Haruka: (It felt like a solid performance... Even if we didn't end up receiving more offers, it's hard to see why we would get less.)
Haruka: (So, what's going on?)
MEIKO: <You seem concerned, Haruka.>
Haruka: Huh? MEIKO...?
Haruka: Can I help you? Did something happen?
MEIKO: <I feel like you've had a lot on your mind lately. I came to see how you were doing.>
Haruka: Oh...
Haruka: I'm sorry for making you worry.
MEIKO: <Nonsense! Still...>
MEIKO: <Are you bothered by how you haven't been receiving any offers?>
Haruka: Yes, you're spot on.
Haruka: Saito's been looking into that for us, so I need to stay focused on the work in front of me. But my mind keeps wandering back to it...
MEIKO: Haruka...
MEIKO: <Yes, I understand your concern... You were receiving more and more offers, and they just suddenly stopped.>
Haruka: Exactly...
MEIKO: <I know you're worried, but it's also not good to dwell.>
MEIKO: <We don't know what's actually going on, but I do know that you and the others have been doing everything you can for your fans up until now.>
MEIKO: <Your performances and activities are proof of that. I have to think that you've been making a positive impact on others.>
MEIKO: <So, for now, just keep on moving forward, one step at a time.>
Haruka: Yeah...
Haruka: (MEIKO's absolutely right.)
Haruka: (There's no point in me worrying like this.)
Haruka: (Right now, I should be focusing on spreading as much hope as I can to our fans and giving what's in front of me my best effort.)
Haruka: Thank you, MEIKO.
Haruka: For now, I'll try to focus all my attention on this run.
MEIKO: <Yes, that's what I like to hear. I believe in you, Haruka!>
Haruka: *Nod* Thanks.
Haruka: Alright...
Haruka: (I feel much better now after talking to MEIKO, so I'll keep running and...)
Haruka: (Oh, I know. I might take this opportunity to up my distance a little. Running a new route should help take my mind off what's been happening.)
Haruka: (Choosing this path was a good idea.)
Haruka: (There's plenty of greenery, and the air tastes so fresh. Plus, this sidewalk's easy to run on because it's so nice and wide.)
Haruka: (Maybe I'll run this route again sometime...)
Haruka: Hm? That looks like...
Haruka: Tenma and Shinonome?
Tsukasa: Hm? Isn't that...?
Akito: ...! Haruka Kiritani?
Haruka: Good morning. It's been a while.
Haruka: Can I ask what you two are doing?
Tsukasa: I was doing my morning run, and just so happened to bump into Akito doing the same!
Tsukasa: We were catching up, and enjoying some sparkling conversation!
Akito: Definitely not sparkling.
Akito: Anyway, Kiritani, were you also running just now?
Haruka: Yes, as a part of my daily routine.
Haruka: I don't usually run around here, but I decided to try someplace new and go a little further than normal, since I had a little time.
Tsukasa: Ah, what wonderful work ethic! We should expect no less from a professional idol!
Tsukasa: As a future star, I need to do the same! Let's follow Kiritani's example and run as much as we can today!
Akito: Wait, it's not good to just run until you drop.
Akito: But singing and dancing does require a lot of stamina. In that sense, I guess it's important to train hard every day.
Tsukasa: That's exactly my point! The more stamina you have, the better your practices become!
Haruka: Hehe. I agree. Let's all do our best.
Tsukasa: Yes, let's!
Haruka: Oh, anyway... I need to get back to my run. I'd also like to change before I head to school.
Akito: Yeah, me too.
Tsukasa: Okay, see you at school! Take care, Kiritani!
Haruka: Take care.
Haruka: (They're all doing what they can to make their dreams come true.)
Haruka: (Which means I need to do the same!)
